From: Zijun Hu <zijun.hu@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2025 20:31:18 +0800
Subject: Bluetooth: hci_core: Eliminate an unnecessary goto label in
 hci_find_irk_by_addr()
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
Git-commit: 88d6ba89d86404073dc3cb711203c02b0754b166
References: jsc#PED-14261

Eliminate an unnecessary goto label by using break instead of goto to
exit the loop in hci_find_irk_by_addr().

Signed-off-by: Zijun Hu <zijun.hu@oss.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Acked-by: Chun-Yi Lee <jlee@suse.com>
---
 net/bluetooth/hci_core.c |    4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/net/bluetooth/hci_core.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/hci_core.c
@@ -1256,12 +1256,10 @@ struct smp_irk *hci_find_irk_by_addr(str
 		if (addr_type == irk->addr_type &&
 		    bacmp(bdaddr, &irk->bdaddr) == 0) {
 			irk_to_return = irk;
-			goto done;
+			break;
 		}
 	}
 
-done:
-
 	if (irk_to_return && hci_is_blocked_key(hdev, HCI_BLOCKED_KEY_TYPE_IRK,
 						irk_to_return->val)) {
 		bt_dev_warn_ratelimited(hdev, "Identity key blocked for %pMR",
